---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy | ZeroUpload";
const description =
  "ZeroUpload's privacy policy. Your files are converted entirely in your browser and are never uploaded, stored, or seen by us.";
const updated = "June 2026";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-16 pb-20">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="article-body mt-8 space-y-4 text-stone leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        With most sites, the privacy policy is where they explain everything they
        collect. This one is short for the opposite reason: the converter runs on
        your device, so there isn't much for us to collect. Here's exactly what
        does and doesn't happen to your data.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">1. The short version</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>We never receive your files.</strong> Every conversion happens
        locally, inside your web browser, on your own device. ZeroUpload does not
        operate servers that receive, process, or store the files you convert —
        because the conversion does not require one.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">2. Your files</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li>When you convert a file, it is read into your browser's memory, converted on your device, and offered back to you as a download.</li>
        <li>Your file is <strong>never uploaded</strong> to ZeroUpload or any third party.</li>
        <li>We keep <strong>no copy</strong> of your files, ever. We could not retrieve one if asked — we never had it.</li>
        <li>When you close or refresh the page, the file data is released from memory.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can verify this yourself: start a conversion and then disconnect your
        internet — it will still work — or open your browser's developer Network
        tab and confirm there are no upload requests. (The AI-powered tools — the
        background remover and image upscaler — need a one-time model download
        first; after that they work offline too. See section 5.)
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">3. Information we do collect</h2>
      <p>
        ZeroUpload is a static website. To operate and improve it, we may use:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li><strong>Privacy-respecting, aggregate analytics</strong> to understand anonymous usage (such as which pages are popular and general traffic counts). This never includes the contents of your files and is not used to identify you.</li>
        <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> If the site displays ads, our advertising partners may use cookies or similar technologies as described in their own privacy policies. You can control cookies through your browser settings. Ads never receive your files.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not require accounts, and we do not ask for or store personal
        information such as your name or email to use the converter.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">4. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The core converter works without requiring cookies. Any cookies used are
        limited to basic site functionality and, where applicable, advertising
        partners. You can block or delete cookies in your browser settings at any
        time.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">5. Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        The site is hosted on a content delivery network (CDN) that serves the
        static pages and conversion engine files. Like all web hosts, the CDN may
        process standard technical request data (such as IP address and user
        agent) to deliver the site and protect against abuse. This is standard web
        infrastructure and does not involve your converted files.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>AI-powered tools.</strong> The background remover and the image
        upscaler run an AI model directly in your browser. The first time you use
        one, your browser downloads the model file once from a third-party AI
        model host (Hugging Face's CDN); after that it is cached on your device.
        Downloading the model involves a normal web request to that host, but
        <strong>your image is still never uploaded</strong> — only the model
        comes down to your device, and all processing happens locally.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">6. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        ZeroUpload is a general-purpose utility and is not directed at children
        under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">7. Your rights (GDPR / CCPA)</h2>
      <p>
        Because we do not collect or store your files or personal account data,
        there is nothing of yours for us to export or delete. For any questions
        about data the CDN or advertising partners may process, contact us and we
        will help where we can.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
        reflected by the "Last updated" date above.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Email <strong>support@zeroupload.app</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-body :global(strong) {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
